textBeforeTable: Marine Biology Capstone Full term (4 credits) To select the correct CRN, please choose your major and track.  Then select your major advisor. PhD students register for directed studies if their proposal has not been approved. Once a proposal has been approved by the Director, MS students sequentially register for and complete credits in each succeeding terms until the capstone/thesis is complete and has been successfully defended.  If a student fails to register for any given term without written approval by the Associate Dean, that student will be withdrawn from the program. MS students wishing to register for Capstone or Thesis Credits must have had their proposal accepted by the Oceanographic Center Program Office.    A student who has not had their proposal approved by the program office may have to register for a Directed Independent Study and must contact the Program Office for the Course Reference Number (CRN) associated with their major advisor. Capstone, Thesis, Ph.D. Directed Study, and Dissertation Credits Electives will open up to the student body 2 weeks after registration starts. Core courses will be available to non-Coastal Zone Management students 2 weeks before the start of classes.
